Patch summary:
Fix gfxstream guest Vulkan rendering on Apple Silicon/Asahi by preserving the
host modifier path for DRM-format image queries and by carrying Android's
AHardwareBuffer layout-preservation workaround into sync2 pipeline barriers.
Without these guards, ANGLE/Chromium can create native-buffer surfaces whose
contents are discarded or whose attachment usage is stripped, leaving Vulkan
accelerated web content black. Also expose gfxstream-backed Vulkan 1.4 and
Android profile capability extensions whose dispatch and feature structs are
already generated, and report the EAC linear-transfer bits required by the
Android baseline CPU-only Vulkan profile. Complete the gfxstream guest's BGRA
AHardwareBuffer mappings as well, allowing ANGLE to import Android cursor-plane
buffers instead of rejecting format 5 as an invalid external format.

